==In popular culture==
{{Main|Neanderthals in popular culture}}
Neanderthals have been portrayed in popular culture including appearances in literature, visual media and comedy. Early 20th century artistic interpretations often presented Neanderthals as beastly creatures, emphasising hairiness and rough, dark complexion.<ref>[http://www.yorku.ca/kdenning/images/kupka.jpg Neanderthal image by Kupka, based on Boule, 1909], in [http://www.yorku.ca/kdenning/+2140%202005-6/2140-15Nov2005.htm Humanity's Journeys Dr. Kathryn Denning, 2005]. Retrieved March 17, 2012.</ref>

