{{Infobox book |name = Sensibility Objectified: The Sculptures of Sarbari Roy Choudhury |title_orig = |translator = |image = Sensibility Objectified.jpg|caption = |author = [[R. Siva Kumar]] |illustrator = |cover_artist = |country = [[India]] |language = English |series = |subject = Art |genre = |publisher = Mapin Publishing |pub_date = February 16, 2010 |english_pub_date = |pages = 136 |isbn = 1890206032 |oclc = |preceded_by = |followed_by = }}
'''''Sensibility Objectified: The Sculptures of Sarbari Roy Choudhury''''' is a book by [[R. Siva Kumar]] that discusses the life and sculptures of [[Sarbari Roy Choudhury]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Sensibility-Objectified-Scluptures-Sarbari-Choudhury/dp/1890206032|title=Sensibility Objectified: The Scupltures of Sarbari Roy Choudhury|first=Siva R.|last=Kumar|date=16 February 2010|publisher=Mapin Publishing Gp Pty Ltd|via=Amazon}}</ref> According to [[R. Siva kumar]] the 'sculptural sensibility' of [[Sarbari Roy Choudhury]], represented in his figurative and animated works, reveals the artist’s connection with the Indian traditions of sculpture, despite being strongly influenced by the West.
Some of Roy's best works are of classical musicians—[[Bade Ghulam Ali Khan]], [[Ali Akbar Khan]], [[Siddheshwari Devi]] and [[Kesarbai Kerkar]]. Starting from the 1950s, the monograph traces his work of each decade, revealing the artistic journey of one of India’s leading sculptors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mapinpub.in/bookinfo.php?id=189#visit|title=Sensibility Objectified|website=mapinpub.in}}</ref>
